# Flowboard — environment template. Copy to .env.local. Never commit .env* files.
# Real values live only in host dashboards (Vercel) and GitHub Actions secrets.
#
# Local dev + CI use `supabase start` (a local Supabase stack); its URL and anon
# key are printed by `npx supabase status`. In prod, use your Supabase project's
# Project URL and anon / publishable key (Dashboard → Project Settings → API).

# ---- Supabase (public, browser-safe — inlined into the client bundle at build) ----
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-or-publishable-key

# That is all the app needs: every read goes through the anon / publishable key
# plus Row-Level Security, and the public demo board is world-readable — so there
# is no service-role key to configure or leak.
